               <head>Miscellany containing four separate works</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>A volume described on the binding as 
            <title>Kitāb-i mujmal al-uṣūl</title>containing astrological and Zoroastrian works. The copyist is probably Siyāvakhsh ibn Ūrmazdyār (f. 39v)
                  </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2001000141" n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_220-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="24v"/>
                     <title key="work_21890" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Jāmah-i ikhtiyārāt</title>
                     <title key="work_21890" xml:lang="fa">جامه اختیارات</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8086">Ṣafī ibn Muḥammad Munajjam Jīlī Lāḥijī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8086">صفی ابن محمد منجم جیلی لاحجی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>An astrological compilation in Persian ascribed to Ṣafī ibn Muḥammad Munajjam Jīlī Lāḥijī from various authors in 82 chapters with a khāṭimah.</p>
                        <p>Followed by a table (f.24v) of ascendants for important cities.</p>
                        <p>Headings in red. 16 lines per page.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2001000141" n="2" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_220-item2">
                     <locus from="27v" to="33r"/>
                     <note>
                        <p>An untitled Persain treatise without author on the astrolabe, followed (ff. 28v-33r) by astronomical and astrological tables.</p>
                        <p>Headings in red. 16 lines per page.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85038589" n="3" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_220-item3">
                     <locus from="34r" to="37v"/>
                     <note>
                        <p>A poem on the significance of tinglings and twitchings of different parts of the body.</p>
                        <p>Headings in red. In 4 columns, 13-14 lines per page.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85150018" n="4" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_220-item4">
                     <locus from="39r" to="40v"/>
                     <note>
                        <p>Part of an unidentified Zoroastrian work.</p>
                        <p>The copyist's name, Siyāvakhsh ibn Ūrmazdyār and genealogy is given in full on f. 39v.</p>
                        <p>Headings in red.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85150018" n="5" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_220-item5">
                     <locus from="41r" to="56r"/>
                     <note>
                        <p>Prayers and instructions in Persian and Avestan.</p>
                        <p>Folio 54 blank. 14 lines to a page. Headings in red.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ae">Persian &amp; Avestan</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
